snippet.title: Tallow and Marty Timelapse (Amber Haze)
snippet.description:
Marty - “Señorita Tallow. If I may ask. What do you expect to find here in Kilbrook pass? I’ve heard that it’s $10,000 for your head. If you’re looking for refuge, I’m afraid you’ve come to the wrong place, mi cariño.”

Tallow - “Lawmen sniff around here often?”

Marty - “Not lawmen… Redtowns. I suggest you keep your head down, ¿vale?”

Tallow - “I’ll take that into heart, amigo.”

Marty - “I’m flattered that you think we are friends. I cannot seem to think of anyone else I’ve been able to say that to. At least not any more…”

Tallow - “Well, friends are useful in a place like this, don’t ya think?”

Marty - “Well, Ms Tallow. There’s a difference between those who are truly your friend and those who just want to use you. Friends don’t have a ‘use’. Friends have a purpose. And that purpose is to be your friend.”

Marty and Tallow meet in person for the first time to share a nice conversation. Considering that Marty is older and wiser than Tallow, he shares his wisdom with her about living off the land and how she should handle relationships. They meet in the desert town of Kilbrook pass, which lawmen know as the town which houses the deadliest outlaws. Many lawmen refuse to investigate due to their lack of jurisdiction and gun power. Many detectives from private agencies sniff around, so outlaws in this town have to be careful about who they speak to.

Song: Bjorn Olsson - Annika
